WEBVTT

00:18.017 --> 00:21.312
-[Joe] Previously on You:
-Get your hands off me!

00:21.938 --> 00:23.898
-I'm Ryan Goodwin.
-Go.

00:25.400 --> 00:28.236
-If something's wrong, tell me.
-I'm buying a vineyard.

00:28.903 --> 00:32.073
My dad is a lot worse than I thought.
I went into his office.

00:32.157 --> 00:36.244
And he has
all this insane conspiracy shit,

00:36.327 --> 00:37.954
including you and Joe.

00:38.038 --> 00:39.456
We are a team.

00:41.708 --> 00:42.959
The best team.

00:50.508 --> 00:52.802
[Joe] Marriage is a game.

00:52.886 --> 00:54.554
["Feel Good" playing]

00:54.637 --> 00:56.431
When things are going well,

00:56.514 --> 00:59.809
my wife and I are on the same side,
an unshakable team.

01:01.061 --> 01:02.479
♪ Sometimes you just wanna ♪

01:02.562 --> 01:04.898
-♪ Feel good, feel good ♪
-♪ You know I like to ♪

01:04.981 --> 01:07.525
-♪ Feel good, feel good ♪
-♪ I love it when you ♪

01:07.609 --> 01:09.736
-♪ Feel good, feel good ♪
-♪ Hit it ♪

01:09.819 --> 01:11.696
-Love in the Time of Cholera?
-You got it.

01:11.780 --> 01:14.866
-Oh, my God! That is impossible.
-Yeah!

01:14.949 --> 01:17.368
-Go do it. Be better.
-Okay, I got this.

01:17.452 --> 01:20.705
-[Joe] Right now, my game...
-We are so good at this.

01:20.789 --> 01:23.041
...is being a good husband-- No, no.

01:23.124 --> 01:24.584
No, the best husband,

01:24.667 --> 01:28.338
so Love doesn't get suspicious
about what's really going on.

01:28.421 --> 01:32.342
That I can't stop thinking about you,
Marienne.

01:33.051 --> 01:37.555
It's been two days
since our sprinkler-soaked night.

01:37.639 --> 01:41.309
You haven't texted, but I know better
than to overplay my hand.

01:41.392 --> 01:42.727
[all laughing]

02:12.882 --> 02:13.842
[cell phone chimes]

02:50.920 --> 02:54.465
All right, so far, so good.
He's gonna meet me to talk.

02:54.549 --> 02:56.718
[Joe]
If I wasn't so in love with you, Marienne,

02:56.801 --> 02:59.012
I might find this more upsetting,

02:59.095 --> 03:03.182
but as it stands,
I have to play just jealous enough.

03:03.266 --> 03:05.602
You had to deploy your lace bra for that?

03:07.186 --> 03:08.021
Yeah.

03:09.439 --> 03:14.611
I know it's all a bit spooky, but...
It also kind of feels like no big deal.

03:14.694 --> 03:18.323
[Joe] Is it just me
or doth the lady protest kind of a lot?

03:18.406 --> 03:21.910
The sooner we find out
what Matthew could have on us,

03:21.993 --> 03:25.038
if anything,
the sooner we can fix it, right?

03:25.121 --> 03:27.999
[Joe] She might be more attracted to Theo
than she's willing to admit,

03:28.082 --> 03:29.751
but she's also right and distracted,

03:29.834 --> 03:33.463
which is necessary to keep her
from Spidey-sensing you. Speaking of...

03:33.546 --> 03:37.050
Oh, the library fundraiser is coming up.

03:37.133 --> 03:41.679
My boss asked me to stay late
the next couple of nights.

03:41.763 --> 03:43.473
Uh, I would have said no.

03:43.556 --> 03:46.392
But I think that will make her
even more irritable than usual,

03:46.476 --> 03:48.228
so I hope that's okay.

03:48.311 --> 03:52.690
Yeah. I mean, of course. Should I...?
Should I put it in my calendar?

03:52.774 --> 03:54.901
[Joe] And have you both cross? No, no, no.

03:54.984 --> 03:59.113
It'll be pretty boring.
I wouldn't want to inflict that upon you.

04:00.949 --> 04:03.451
How'd I end up
with such a thoughtful husband?

04:03.534 --> 04:05.161
[Joe] This game is tricky.

04:05.245 --> 04:07.372
Juggling you and Love won't be easy.

04:07.455 --> 04:11.918
But if this is the game I have to play
to get closer to you, then game on.

04:22.220 --> 04:24.764
[Joe] Though you haven't texted me back,
Marienne,

04:24.847 --> 04:27.225
I know you felt what I felt in the rain.

04:27.308 --> 04:28.768
This seems elaborate.

04:28.851 --> 04:31.980
Yeah, and Alice in Wonderland,
a story dear

04:32.063 --> 04:35.692
to friends-of-the-library chairwoman
Sherry Conrad, which is fabulous...

04:35.775 --> 04:38.736
[Joe] You feel it right now.
You're pretending you don't.

04:38.820 --> 04:41.656
And don't get me started
on how the friends of the library

04:41.739 --> 04:43.992
only visit the library
when there's a gala.

04:44.075 --> 04:46.869
[Joe] You're cautious about us,
which is smart.

04:46.953 --> 04:49.497
But it means
I need to be a little bit bold.

04:49.580 --> 04:51.207
I thought about you all weekend.

04:52.709 --> 04:53.835
Really?

04:53.918 --> 04:54.836
Um...

04:57.005 --> 05:02.093
'Cause I couldn't stop thinking
about those goats that faint

05:02.176 --> 05:03.636
when they're startled.

05:03.720 --> 05:06.222
You know, like, what the fuck, Darwin?

05:08.141 --> 05:10.685
-I thought about you too. A lot.
-[Joe] I knew it.

05:10.768 --> 05:13.604
-But it can't happen again.
-[Joe] And here's the speech.

05:13.688 --> 05:17.066
Look, I gave it a lot of thought,
and for so many reasons,

05:17.150 --> 05:20.403
-first and foremost being you're married--
-That's true.

05:20.486 --> 05:23.114
But it's not that simple, I promise you.

05:26.617 --> 05:27.577
I understand.

05:27.660 --> 05:30.538
...that if I push too hard,
I risk losing you.

05:30.621 --> 05:31.956
Mommy.

05:32.040 --> 05:34.125
Hey, no running, remember?

05:34.959 --> 05:37.295
Ryan surprised me
by dropping her here this morning,

05:37.378 --> 05:39.255
but she's having so much fun helping out.

05:39.339 --> 05:42.091
-Aren't you, mon petit chou?
-[Joe] I didn't think it was possible,

05:42.175 --> 05:45.094
but in her presence,
you are even more exquisite.

05:45.178 --> 05:46.554
You must be Juliette.

05:46.637 --> 05:47.805
Hmm?

05:49.265 --> 05:51.809
-Look what Dante found for me.
-Oh.

05:51.893 --> 05:55.730
Is that Hans Christian Andersen?
Let me guess. Little Mermaid fan.

05:55.813 --> 05:56.647
Hey, Dante.

05:56.731 --> 05:57.565
Hey.

05:57.648 --> 05:58.608
Aw.

05:59.317 --> 06:03.905
-Why aren't you wearing your glasses?
-Yeah. Someone was doing cartwheels.

06:03.988 --> 06:08.951
Okay, we're going to have
to get these fixed before your dad sees.

06:09.035 --> 06:10.328
I can cover for you.

06:10.411 --> 06:14.332
Thanks, but my car is in the shop.

06:14.415 --> 06:15.541
Let me take you.

06:16.334 --> 06:17.752
Does he have to come?

06:17.835 --> 06:19.921
[Joe] Ouch. What'd I do to her?

06:20.004 --> 06:23.674
Sorry. Yes, that would be great.

06:24.509 --> 06:25.885
-Thank you.
-[cell phone buzzes]

06:26.469 --> 06:28.471
Hey. I'll get back to it.

06:28.554 --> 06:30.431
-Hey.
-Mom still hasn't shown up

06:30.515 --> 06:31.891
and she won't answer my calls.

06:31.974 --> 06:34.435
Isn't today the meeting
to finalize her divorce?

06:34.519 --> 06:37.355
Yeah, three hours ago. I mean, she flaked.

06:38.397 --> 06:39.315
Classic Dottie.

06:39.398 --> 06:42.193
[sighs] Any chance you could watch Henry?

06:42.276 --> 06:43.986
[Joe] Me, you and our kids,

06:44.070 --> 06:46.656
it's not exactly the quality time
I had in mind today,

06:46.739 --> 06:49.242
but what would the perfect husband do?

06:49.325 --> 06:51.244
Sure. I'll be there soon.

06:52.703 --> 06:55.540
-Okay. Thanks.
-[knocking on door]

06:57.458 --> 06:59.544
-Hi.
-I'm sorry to pop by like this,

06:59.627 --> 07:02.505
-but I just heard something terrible.
-What?

07:03.548 --> 07:07.135
My caterer, for the library fundraiser,
got frostbite.

07:07.218 --> 07:08.928
-Too much infrared sauna.
-Oh, my God.

07:09.011 --> 07:13.182
So she's out.
Then I realized, you could fill in.

07:13.266 --> 07:14.142
Oh.

07:15.309 --> 07:18.521
I mean, that's really flattering,

07:18.604 --> 07:21.023
but I haven't catered in a long time.

07:21.107 --> 07:23.818
Don't be silly.
I'm sure it's like riding a Peloton.

07:23.901 --> 07:25.403
I have to develop a menu.

07:25.486 --> 07:28.656
-I'd have to hire people.
-I will handle staff and logistics.

07:28.739 --> 07:30.533
You do the food,

07:30.616 --> 07:33.870
collect the compliments,
get exposure for your business.

07:34.871 --> 07:35.955
Don't make me beg.

07:39.584 --> 07:43.129
-Okay.
-Mm! Thank you, thank you, thank you.

07:44.589 --> 07:45.798
Mm...

07:46.382 --> 07:49.051
-What?
-You have a glow about you

07:49.135 --> 07:51.012
and I noticed it on game night too.

07:51.095 --> 07:52.138
Yeah, I mean...

07:53.764 --> 07:54.932
I took your advice.

07:55.016 --> 07:57.727
-About choosing your soul mate.
-Mm.

07:57.810 --> 08:00.730
Joe has been so attentive lately.

08:00.813 --> 08:03.858
I love that. And the sex life?

08:03.941 --> 08:05.860
Back on track, I assume?

08:07.278 --> 08:09.822
[tsking] No. I don't mean to pry.

08:09.906 --> 08:11.949
No, Joe's just been really busy with work.

08:12.033 --> 08:14.368
No judgment. Have you seen the studies

08:14.452 --> 08:17.538
on how quickly
our sex parts get bored of each other?

08:17.622 --> 08:22.043
But, you know,
it doesn't have to be an issue.

08:23.127 --> 08:25.129
You are so hot, Love.

08:25.755 --> 08:27.840
-Just hack your sex life.
-Like...

08:28.549 --> 08:29.759
with supplements?

08:30.927 --> 08:34.472
A lot of ways to increase Joe's libido.

08:35.139 --> 08:38.518
Tap into his fantasies,
really make him feel like a man.

08:38.601 --> 08:42.730
It's what I've done with Cary,
and my vagina has never been happier.

08:42.813 --> 08:45.566
Look, I'll send you a post
I wrote about it.

08:45.650 --> 08:48.528
Along with an RSVP list of the guests

08:48.611 --> 08:50.238
-with food allergies.
-Okay.

08:50.321 --> 08:51.822
Thanks again.

08:51.906 --> 08:53.366
[chuckling]

08:53.449 --> 08:54.575
Whoo!

09:03.125 --> 09:05.920
-Oh, my God.
-Sorry. Sorry. I know, I'm early.

09:06.003 --> 09:08.422
-Yeah. Thank you for meeting me.
-Yeah.

09:08.506 --> 09:12.593
Oh, that's--
That's not why I asked you here.

09:12.677 --> 09:13.636
Okay.

09:15.721 --> 09:16.597
Um...

09:16.681 --> 09:22.061
Sorry, I feel like there's mixed signals,
'cause, like, first, we have sex.

09:22.144 --> 09:24.647
-Can you--?
-It's all right. And then you know...

09:25.815 --> 09:28.150
You say that it can't happen again,

09:28.234 --> 09:32.697
and then you're, like,
stripping at your window,

09:32.780 --> 09:35.074
asking me to meet in secret.

09:35.157 --> 09:36.367
Yeah, you're right.

09:38.035 --> 09:40.496
You're right. I'm a mess.

09:40.580 --> 09:44.375
I guess this is what happens
when your parents get divorced

09:44.458 --> 09:46.961
and you see how easily
your own marriage can fall apart.

09:47.044 --> 09:49.880
-Are you and Joe--?
-Oh, no, no, no.

09:49.964 --> 09:51.674
-I shouldn't have said anything.
-Hey.

09:52.383 --> 09:53.593
You're not alone.

09:54.552 --> 09:55.845
Honestly, like,

09:57.054 --> 09:58.097
we're friends.

09:58.806 --> 10:02.476
I'm your friend, if you need anything.

10:04.645 --> 10:05.813
Okay.

10:08.774 --> 10:09.609
I mean...

10:11.402 --> 10:14.405
-if you really wanna help...
-Mm-hm?

10:14.488 --> 10:17.283
Could you find out
what your dad has on me and Joe?

10:17.366 --> 10:21.203
What--? What do you mean?
What does he have?

10:21.287 --> 10:23.247
-I don't know. That's the thing.
-Okay.

10:24.123 --> 10:25.750
Then-- Then why?

10:26.584 --> 10:27.877
I-- I mean--

10:28.711 --> 10:32.214
We've talked about this.
My family's in the public eye.

10:32.298 --> 10:35.343
My parents are chopping off
each other's heads in this divorce.

10:35.426 --> 10:39.013
-It shouldn't make my family interesting--
-If it's not like a literal crime,

10:39.096 --> 10:43.309
-he's not gonna show anyone.
-But this is a major trigger for me.

10:43.392 --> 10:46.812
I can't help but worry
when people have information on my family.

10:50.066 --> 10:53.027
-I know it's not rational--
-It doesn't have to be.

10:53.110 --> 10:54.570
I get it. I do.

10:56.197 --> 10:59.408
-People are fucking vampires.
-[chuckles]

10:59.492 --> 11:01.869
You know, that can scar you for sure.

11:01.952 --> 11:03.037
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

11:04.789 --> 11:05.665
Yeah.

11:07.041 --> 11:07.958
You get it.

11:12.338 --> 11:16.592
Yeah, okay. Yeah, well, you know,
I'll sneak into his office.

11:17.635 --> 11:18.928
See what I can find.

11:23.391 --> 11:24.225
Thank you.

11:30.314 --> 11:32.274
[Joe] What's your favorite fairy tale?

11:32.358 --> 11:34.235
-[Marienne] Jack and the Beanstalk.
-No.

11:34.318 --> 11:37.530
Yes. Hell, yes. Jack was a little badass.

11:37.613 --> 11:41.700
I wanted to be him. Screw princesses.
I know I wanted to...

11:44.954 --> 11:51.710
[Joe] How do I make you see
I could be your happily ever after?

11:54.755 --> 11:58.592
Hey, can I say something?
And you don't have to say anything back.

12:00.052 --> 12:03.764
It's been a long time
since I have felt this happy.

12:03.848 --> 12:06.809
This feels so easy.
So I just wanna say thank you.

12:08.310 --> 12:10.312
Can we go back to the library?

12:10.896 --> 12:15.818
Baby, your glasses aren't ready yet.

12:15.901 --> 12:18.863
You wanna play a game?
We can play "I Spy."

12:18.946 --> 12:19.780
Okay.

12:20.406 --> 12:23.367
Uh, I spy with my little eye...

12:24.660 --> 12:28.080
something that begins with the letter M.

12:29.039 --> 12:30.416
-It's Mommy.
-Yeah.

12:32.042 --> 12:33.377
Good job, baby.

12:33.461 --> 12:39.383
[Joe] You're thinking what I am.
Is this the family we were destined for?

12:39.467 --> 12:40.593
[cell phone chimes]

12:44.805 --> 12:46.056
What's wrong?

12:46.140 --> 12:49.351
Um, it's... It's Ryan.

12:49.435 --> 12:51.687
He's giving me a heads-up

12:51.770 --> 12:55.399
that Channel Three is making
a sizable donation to the library

12:55.483 --> 12:58.652
and he will be at the fundraiser
to present the check.

12:59.236 --> 13:01.322
You don't think it's a coincidence?

13:01.405 --> 13:04.450
