-Oh.

36:12.545 --> 36:14.964
Sorry, it's my babysitter.

36:17.508 --> 36:18.342
What the fuck?

36:26.225 --> 36:27.894
-I'm so sorry.
-Yeah.

36:32.899 --> 36:34.275
[cell phone ringing]

36:37.320 --> 36:39.739
Let's hang up on your mother.

36:39.822 --> 36:41.616
We don't need to speak to her.

36:42.909 --> 36:44.285
Thank you.

36:45.536 --> 36:47.955
Stephanie, what a pretty name.

36:50.124 --> 36:52.251
Oh, don't worry, he's not a baby.

36:53.044 --> 36:56.797
No, no, he's the reincarnation
of my son, Forty,

36:56.881 --> 36:58.674
and he loves a good taco.

36:58.758 --> 37:00.343
Don't you, baby? Yes.

37:00.426 --> 37:04.013
My daughter's trying to keep him from me.
She's selfish like her father.

37:04.096 --> 37:06.182
I think we're missing
a couple of "gordatas."

37:06.265 --> 37:07.266
Uh--

37:07.350 --> 37:10.394
-They're coming right out.
-Bless you, Persephone.

37:11.312 --> 37:14.273
-You're a good person, aren't you?
-I guess.

37:15.066 --> 37:19.153
I just want Love to understand
where I'm coming from,

37:19.237 --> 37:21.489
but she refuses to listen.

37:21.572 --> 37:24.283
No one will listen.

37:26.869 --> 37:27.703
Except you.

37:28.454 --> 37:31.207
-[car horn honks]
-I'm getting my gordatas.

37:31.999 --> 37:32.917
Chrissake.

37:33.000 --> 37:34.919
No, I need my power back.

37:35.670 --> 37:38.839
I need justice. I need karmic retribution.

37:40.466 --> 37:44.553
-Do you want hot sauce?
-I want all the hot sauce and a lighter.

37:45.304 --> 37:46.430
Excuse me?

37:46.514 --> 37:48.307
I'll give you...

37:49.350 --> 37:51.727
300 dollars for a lighter.

38:04.073 --> 38:05.491
Thank you for listening.

38:09.078 --> 38:10.079
Let's go.

38:10.788 --> 38:12.748
[rock music playing over speakers]

38:17.962 --> 38:19.297
[sirens wailing]

38:24.510 --> 38:25.511
Oh, yeah.

38:27.054 --> 38:29.056
The bastard wanted the vineyard.

38:33.436 --> 38:35.479
-[Henry crying]
-Oh, oh!

38:35.563 --> 38:38.441
Hey, hey, hey. You're okay.

38:41.986 --> 38:44.947
[Joe] Note to self,
if you take a baby on a drunk joyride

38:45.031 --> 38:48.117
to go burn down a vineyard,
make sure you're a rich, white lady

38:48.200 --> 38:50.786
whose lawyer can get you
in a fancy rehab instead of jail.

38:50.870 --> 38:54.165
-Thank you for--
-What the fuck were you thinking?

38:54.248 --> 38:57.209
Just put him to bed, okay? I've got this.

39:12.808 --> 39:14.435
You can sleep here tonight.

39:14.518 --> 39:17.146
Tomorrow, Joe will drive you to rehab.

39:18.064 --> 39:19.273
You'll never see me.

39:20.816 --> 39:23.194
And you will never see Henry ever again.

39:24.278 --> 39:26.864
-You don't mean that.
-I do. With every fiber of my being.

39:26.947 --> 39:30.659
Love, please. I made a mistake.
But I've been punished--

39:30.743 --> 39:32.495
You could have killed him!

39:34.914 --> 39:36.582
You had your family...

39:37.500 --> 39:39.251
and look what you did.

39:39.794 --> 39:43.672
You let your husband destroy
your self-worth.

39:44.465 --> 39:48.469
You neglected your children.
You didn't protect Forty. I did that.

39:48.552 --> 39:49.762
Oh, that's rich.

39:51.389 --> 39:52.598
You liked him broken

39:52.681 --> 39:54.850
-'cause it gave you purpose.
-Maybe.

39:56.519 --> 40:00.064
But I have a new purpose now
and that's protecting my family.

40:01.107 --> 40:04.276
-From you. [laughs]
-How can you say that? I'm your mother.

40:07.238 --> 40:09.407
Having no mother would be better.

40:15.079 --> 40:19.500
You think you're so much better than me?
You're just me 20 years ago.

40:20.960 --> 40:23.295
One day, you will lose everything too.

40:23.379 --> 40:26.006
And then you'll see
how cruel you really are.

40:35.015 --> 40:36.642
Oh. Hey.

40:36.725 --> 40:39.520
Did you get it done? Whatever it is.

40:39.603 --> 40:41.605
Yep, just finished up.

40:42.314 --> 40:44.442
So, what were you doing?

40:44.525 --> 40:48.154
He totally passed out.
Think he really needs some rest.

40:52.825 --> 40:58.664
Look, it's none of my business,
but your dad is not okay.

41:00.833 --> 41:01.917
He needs help.

41:03.169 --> 41:04.420
I'll let myself out.

41:08.132 --> 41:10.926
[door opens, then closes]

41:12.428 --> 41:13.888
["Numb" playing]

42:04.271 --> 42:09.735
[Joe] I should be in bed with you,
tracing and drawing on your arm.

42:09.818 --> 42:14.949
Instead, I'm driving an Uber
shuttling Medusa-in-law to rehab.

42:16.200 --> 42:18.577
Bet you're happy
you won't have to see me anymore.

42:20.871 --> 42:23.415
I always thought
we had a good relationship.

42:28.212 --> 42:30.464
I have something to tell you, Joe.

42:31.840 --> 42:36.053
I see how hard you're trying
to make your marriage work, just like me.

42:36.720 --> 42:38.931
I did everything
to keep my family together,

42:39.014 --> 42:42.101
including lying to myself
about who my husband was...

42:42.768 --> 42:44.144
and who my daughter is.

42:44.228 --> 42:47.398
[Joe] Is this where Dottie tries
to poison me against Love?

42:47.481 --> 42:49.233
Her final act of revenge?

42:49.316 --> 42:51.777
How much do you know
about Love's first husband, James?

42:53.028 --> 42:53.904
Um...

42:54.321 --> 42:58.284
I know they were in love. Married young.

42:58.951 --> 43:01.328
He got cancer and then he died.

43:02.288 --> 43:03.289
Not quite.

43:04.665 --> 43:07.835
When James became ill,
he and Love were already having problems.

43:07.918 --> 43:10.337
After he went into remission,

43:10.421 --> 43:11.797
he asked for a divorce.

43:11.880 --> 43:15.342
And the next thing you know, he was dead.

43:15.426 --> 43:17.344
[Joe] Surely, she's not suggesting...

43:17.428 --> 43:20.764
I have no proof, of course.
Just a mother's intuition.

43:21.682 --> 43:23.392
You probably think I'm crazy.

43:23.475 --> 43:28.355
[Joe] I might, if I hadn't seen
what Love is capable of, many times.

43:28.439 --> 43:29.940
This must be hard.

43:30.566 --> 43:31.775
You're loyal.

43:32.401 --> 43:34.111
That's what makes you a good husband.

43:35.237 --> 43:39.408
But Love has no loyalty
for anyone but herself.

43:40.826 --> 43:44.788
If anything were to happen to you,
I'd never forgive myself.

43:51.920 --> 43:53.589
Like a young Gregory Peck.

43:55.591 --> 43:58.052
[Joe]
Could Love have killed her first husband?

43:58.844 --> 44:03.349
I've been so worried about her hurting you
that I failed to remember:

44:03.432 --> 44:05.309
I am also fair game.

44:17.363 --> 44:21.533
[Joe] But we should be together, Marienne.
I will find a way.

44:21.617 --> 44:25.663
It's risky, but love requires
a hint of madness.

44:25.746 --> 44:28.457
We're all mad here, right, red rose?

44:28.540 --> 44:29.917
-Hey.
-Hey.

44:30.000 --> 44:31.877
-Is everything okay?
-No.

44:38.884 --> 44:41.804
Juliette told Ryan
that we spent the day together.

44:41.887 --> 44:43.806
He's threatening to use it against me.

44:43.889 --> 44:46.517
What? We're just colleagues.

44:46.600 --> 44:49.061
We're not. And you know that.

44:49.144 --> 44:50.938
And besides, it doesn't matter

44:51.021 --> 44:53.941
because Ryan will make it look
as bad as possible.

44:54.024 --> 44:56.777
[Joe] Fucking Ryan. I'll destroy him.

44:56.860 --> 44:58.612
-We can fix this.
-We?

44:59.822 --> 45:02.157
What are you talking about?
You're married.

45:02.241 --> 45:05.869
Your marriage doesn't seem strained.
Your wife is lovely.

45:05.953 --> 45:09.623
[Joe] Lovely, yes. With a mild habit
of murdering women I care about.

45:09.706 --> 45:12.000
I hated having to lie to her.

45:13.168 --> 45:16.171
I slid into old patterns
and I feel disgusted.

45:16.255 --> 45:17.214
I...

45:18.090 --> 45:19.883
It's not good for my recovery.

45:19.967 --> 45:23.929
I'm at a point where I'm supposed to live
with integrity. I can't be a home-wrecker.

45:24.930 --> 45:26.056
Of course not.

45:27.307 --> 45:29.226
But there has to be another way.

45:29.309 --> 45:30.352
There isn't.

45:32.438 --> 45:33.355
Hey.

45:34.606 --> 45:36.859
I care about you. I do.

45:38.485 --> 45:40.779
And, yeah, there's chemistry.

45:40.863 --> 45:41.697
[Joe] But...

45:41.780 --> 45:43.991
But, no, I have to think of Juliette.

45:44.950 --> 45:47.619
And I promised myself,
my next relationship would be...

45:48.620 --> 45:50.706
Would be aboveboard and honest.

45:53.167 --> 45:54.001
I'm sorry.

45:57.296 --> 45:59.798
[Joe] Aboveboard and honest.

45:59.882 --> 46:01.842
How do I give that to you?

46:10.726 --> 46:11.768
You good?

46:12.853 --> 46:15.189
Yeah, yeah, I'm just-- I'm tired.

46:16.398 --> 46:18.650
Can I get your opinion on something?

46:18.734 --> 46:19.693
Yeah, of course.

46:23.030 --> 46:25.365
-What do you think about this?
-What is this?

46:26.158 --> 46:29.244
Sherry sent it.
It's from her secret sex blog.

46:29.828 --> 46:32.581
-Sherry and Cary are in an open marriage.
-Hmm.

46:33.582 --> 46:37.377
And... they wanna sleep with us.

46:42.424 --> 46:44.426
Yeah, I thought it was a joke too.

46:44.510 --> 46:47.179
So--? So why are you showing me this?

46:50.891 --> 46:52.809
As a joke, obviously.

46:52.893 --> 46:53.810
Oh.

46:55.938 --> 46:58.148
You don't really look at me the same.

46:58.232 --> 47:00.484
You don't seem interested
in having sex with me.

47:00.567 --> 47:02.945
That's not true.
People go through rough patches.

47:03.028 --> 47:04.613
I don't wanna become...

47:06.073 --> 47:07.115
like my parents.

47:07.699 --> 47:11.370
They couldn't stay in love.

47:12.496 --> 47:14.498
Maybe we need to shake things up.

47:15.999 --> 47:18.585
It sounds crazy, but I read that article.

47:18.669 --> 47:19.795
[Joe] Opening our marriage.

47:19.878 --> 47:21.880
This loophole cannot be falling
into my lap.

47:21.964 --> 47:24.341
I don't even know how I feel about it.

47:24.424 --> 47:28.220
Sherry just said it was the greatest hack,

47:28.303 --> 47:31.014
and I guess...

47:32.057 --> 47:34.851
Sherry and Cary would be a safe first try.

47:34.935 --> 47:36.937
[Joe] I'd rather take
a chain saw to my thigh,

47:37.020 --> 47:38.438
but hopefully, that's negotiable.

47:38.522 --> 47:40.440
Sorry, I'm just being stupid.

47:40.524 --> 47:43.235
Love, Love, stop, stop, stop backpedaling.

47:45.112 --> 47:46.822
You can come to me with anything.

47:46.905 --> 47:49.575
That's what this marriage is, right?

47:50.158 --> 47:54.121
No idea is too crazy?
We talk things through, right?

47:55.247 --> 47:57.583
And we make decisions together.

48:02.004 --> 48:03.171
I love you.

48:09.136 --> 48:10.971
[Joe] And I love you.

48:19.187 --> 48:20.272
[door locks]

48:26.820 --> 48:29.740
[ominous music playing]

48:39.750 --> 48:41.418
[theme music playing]
